events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 24 points, Miles Bridges added 22 points and 14 rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Oklahoma City Thunder 121-98 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier, Bridges lead Hornets past Thunder 121-98

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 29 points and played exclusively at center in the second half as the Los Angeles Lakers rallied from an eight-point halftime deficit and beat the Orlando Magic 116-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James scores 29, plays center as Lakers rally past Magic

headlines.description: — The 76ers lost the lead — and then their cool.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson completes Clippers' rally past 76ers for 102-101 win

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 28 points, Kevin Huerter added 21 and the Atlanta Hawks won their third straight game after nearly blowing an 18-point lead in a 110-108 victory over the Miami Heat on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 28 as Hawks hold off Heat at the end, 110-108

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jusuf Nurkic grabbed an offensive rebound and hit a shot from the lane with 14 seconds left and the Portland Trail Blazers rallied past the Boston Celtics 109-105 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nurkic's rebound, basket late rally Blazers over Celtics

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 59 seconds to play, and the Toronto Raptors hung on after blowing an 18-point fourth-quarter lead to beat the Washington Wizards 109-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet rescues Raptors late in 109-105 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks displayed a championship mentality by beating a quality opponent even when their shots didn't fall.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 30 as Bucks beat Bulls 94-90

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — James Harden had 37 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds, spoiling Dejounte Murray’s ninth triple-double of the season as the Brooklyn Nets overpowered the San Antonio Spurs 117-102 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden's triple-double helps Nets top Murray, Spurs, 117-102

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 38 points and the Memphis Grizzlies overcame Nikola Jokic's fourth straight triple-double to beat the Denver Nuggets 122-118 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 38, Grizzlies knock off Jokic, Nuggets 122-118

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert scored 24 points, grabbed 13 rebounds and blocked four shots to lead the Utah Jazz to a 111-101 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz snap three-game home skid, beat Pistons 111-101

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Confetti fell and Stephen Curry flexed. He danced and celebrated a January victory against the lowly Rockets as if it were a playoff game in May.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry hits winning jumper, Warriors beat Rockets 105-103
